#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pi"><section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-np1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:2.1"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.1"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
#. <span class="note" hidden>Here, and in the heading to <i lang="pi">nissaggiya pācittiya 3</i> (and also at the end of each of these rules), I translate <i lang="pi">kathina</i> as “robe-making season” rather than “robe-making ceremony,” since this is the contextual meaning in these rules.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:5.1"
msgid "1. Kathinasikkhāpada"
msgstr "1. The training rule on the robe-making season"

#. </h1></div><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.195"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1861"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:6.1"
msgid "Ime kho panāyasmanto tiṃsa nissaggiyā pācittiyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti."
msgstr "Venerables, these thirty rules entailing relinquishment and confession come up for recitation."

#. </p><hr><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:7.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:7.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.1.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1862"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:7.3"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati gotamake cetiye."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī at the Gotamaka Shrine."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:7.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ ticīvaraṃ anuññātaṃ hoti."
msgstr "At that time the Master had allowed the three robes for the monks."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:7.5"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—“bhagavatā ticīvaraṃ anuññātan”ti aññeneva ticīvarena gāmaṃ pavisanti, aññena ticīvarena ārāme acchanti, aññena ticīvarena nahānaṃ otaranti."
msgstr "Knowing that this was the case, monks from the group of six entered the village in one set of three robes, stayed in the monastery in another set, and went to bathe in yet another set."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:7.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:7.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:7.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atirekacīvaraṃ dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can those monks from the group of six keep extra robes?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1863"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they informed the Master. …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:8.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, atirekacīvaraṃ dhārethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you keep extra robes?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:8.3"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:8.4"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them: “…"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.3"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:8.5"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, atirekacīvaraṃ dhāressatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you keep extra robes?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:8.6"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:8.7"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:9.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:9.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu atirekacīvaraṃ dhāreyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk keeps an extra robe(-cloth), he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </strong>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1865"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:10.1"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.196"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato ānandassa atirekacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards a robe was offered to Venerable Ānanda."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.3"
msgid "Āyasmā ca ānando taṃ cīvaraṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa dātukāmo hoti."
msgstr "He wanted to give it to Venerable Sāriputta"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.4"
msgid "Āyasmā ca sāriputto sākete viharati."
msgstr "who was staying at Sāketa."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "Knowing that the Buddha had laid down a rule against keeping an extra robe, Ānanda thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.6"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.7"
msgid "‘na atirekacīvaraṃ dhāretabban’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.8"
msgid "Idañca me atirekacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.9"
msgid "Ahañcimaṃ cīvaraṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa dātukāmo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.10"
msgid "Āyasmā ca sāriputto sākete viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.11"
msgid "Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?"
msgstr "“What should I do in this situation?”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.12"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He informed the Master, and the Master said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.13"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ panānanda, sāriputto āgacchissatī”ti?"
msgstr "“How long is it, Ānanda, before Sāriputta returns?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.14"
msgid "“Navamaṃ vā, bhagavā, divasaṃ dasamaṃ vā”ti."
msgstr "“Nine or ten days, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.15"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.16"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dasāhaparamaṃ atirekacīvaraṃ dhāretuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, you should keep an extra robe for ten days at the most."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:11.17"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:12.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1867"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.5"></a>
#. <span class="note" hidden>In addition to meaning a finished robe, according to the definition of <i lang="pi">cīvara</i> below it also refers to pieces of robe-cloth. This means that I have to vary my translation depending on the context. Sometimes, such as here, the meaning is both robe and robe-cloth, and I then render it as robe(-cloth).</span>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:12.2"
msgid "“Niṭṭhitacīvarasmiṃ bhikkhunā ubbhatasmiṃ kathine dasāhaparamaṃ atirekacīvaraṃ dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘When his robe is finished and the robe-making season has ended, a monk should keep an extra robe(-cloth) for ten days at the most."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:12.3"
msgid "Taṃ atikkāmayato nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:12.4"
msgid "(<em>1</em>:<strong>20</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:13.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.1.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.1.3.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1868"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:13.2"
msgid "Niṭṭhitacīvarasminti"
msgstr "When his robe is finished:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>This refers to the robe-cloth received during the robe-making season. For details see <span class="ref">Mv.7.2-7.12</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:13.3"
msgctxt "bhikkhuno cīvaraṃ kataṃ vā hoti naṭṭhaṃ vā vinaṭṭhaṃ vā daḍḍhaṃ vā cīvarāsā vā upacchinnā."
msgstr "the monk has made a robe, or the robe-cloth has been lost, destroyed, or burnt, or he has abandoned his expectation of receiving further robe-cloth."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1869"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:14.1"
msgid "Ubbhatasmiṃ kathineti"
msgstr "The robe-making season has ended:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>For an explanation of this see <span class="ref">Mv.7.1.7</span> and <span class="ref">Mv.7.2-7.12</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:14.2"
msgctxt "aṭṭhannaṃ mātikānaṃ aññatarāya mātikāya ubbhataṃ hoti, saṃghena vā antarā ubbhataṃ hoti."
msgstr "it has ended according to one of the eight headings or the Order has ended it, whichever comes first."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1870"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:15.1"
msgid "Dasāhaparamanti"
msgstr "For ten days at the most:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:15.2"
msgctxt "dasāhaparamatā dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "it should be kept for ten days at a maximum."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1871"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:16.1"
msgid "Atirekacīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "An extra robe(-cloth):"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>“Transferred” is a rendering of <i lang="pi">vikappita</i>. The explanation given at <i lang="pi">pācittiya</i> 59 seems to make it clear that <i lang="pi">vikappanā</i> refers to a change in ownership. The word commentary specifically says that the item is given to someone else and that the monk giving it up may use it only if he takes their belonging on trust.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:16.2"
msgctxt "anadhiṭṭhitaṃ avikappitaṃ."
msgstr "a robe(-cloth) that is not determined, nor transferred."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1872"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:17.1"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe(-cloth):"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, jute, and hemp, see <span class="ref">Mv.8.3.1</span>.</span>
#. <span class="note" hidden>This means not smaller than 8 by 4 <i lang="pi">sugata</i> finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see <span class="ref">Kkh.94.4</span> and BMC I, pp.565-566.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:17.2"
msgctxt "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ, vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.1.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1873"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.1"
msgid "Taṃ atikkāmayato nissaggiyaṃ hotīti"
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that […] entailing relinquishment:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>According to the commentary this means the tenth dawn after one received the robe(-cloth), see <span class="ref">Sp.3.639.27</span></span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.2"
msgid "ekādase aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "entailing relinquishment at dawn on the eleventh day."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.3"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe(-cloth) should be relinquished to the Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.8"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.5"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching the Order, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.6"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ dasāhātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe(-cloth) which I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.7"
msgid "imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.8"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he is to acknowledge the offense."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.9"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The acknowledgment should be received by a competent and capable monk."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:18.10"
msgid "Nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ—"
msgstr "The relinquished robe(-cloth) is then to be given back:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1874"></a><span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:19.1"
msgid "“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:19.2"
msgid "Idaṃ cīvaraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno nissaggiyaṃ saṃghassa nissaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "This robe(-cloth) which was to be relinquished by monk so-and-so has been relinquished to the Order."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:19.3"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho imaṃ cīvaraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dadeyyā”ti."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should give this robe(-cloth) back to monk so-and-so.’"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.197"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1875"></a><span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:20.1"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā sambahule bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassu vacanīyā—"
msgstr "After approaching several monks, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:20.2"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ dasāhātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe(-cloth) which I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:20.3"
msgid "Imāhaṃ āyasmantānaṃ nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the venerables.’"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:20.4"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he is to acknowledge the offense."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:20.5"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The acknowledgment should be received by a competent and capable monk."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:20.6"
msgid "Nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ—"
msgstr "The relinquished robe(-cloth) is then to be given back:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1876"></a><span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:21.1"
msgid "“Suṇantu me āyasmantā."
msgstr "‘Let the venerables listen to me."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:21.2"
msgid "Idaṃ cīvaraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno nissaggiyaṃ āyasmantānaṃ nissaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "This robe(-cloth) which was to be relinquished by monk so-and-so has been relinquished to you."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.9"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:21.3"
msgid "Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, āyasmantā imaṃ cīvaraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dadeyyun”ti."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to you, you should give this robe(-cloth) back to monk so-and-so.’"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1877"></a><span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:22.1"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching a single monk, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:22.2"
msgid "“idaṃ me, āvuso, cīvaraṃ dasāhātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘This robe(-cloth) which I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:22.3"
msgid "Imāhaṃ āyasmato nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to you.’"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:22.4"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he is to acknowledge the offense."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:22.5"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The acknowledgment should be received by that monk."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:22.6"
msgid "Nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ—"
msgstr "The relinquished robe(-cloth) is then to be given back:"

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:22.7"
msgid "“imaṃ cīvaraṃ āyasmato dammī”ti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe(-cloth) back to you.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.1.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1878"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.2"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante atikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days and he perceives it as more than ten days, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.3"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante vematiko, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.4"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante anatikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days, but he perceives it as less than ten days, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.5"
msgid "Anadhiṭṭhite adhiṭṭhitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is undetermined, but he perceives it as determined, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.6"
msgid "Avikappite vikappitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is not transferred, but he perceives it as transferred, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.7"
msgid "Avissajjite vissajjitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is not given away, but he perceives it as given away, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.8"
msgid "Anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is not lost, but he perceives it as lost, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.9"
msgid "Avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is not destroyed, but he perceives it as destroyed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.10"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.10"
msgid "Adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is not burnt, but he perceives it as burnt, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:23.11"
msgid "Avilutte viluttasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is not stolen, but he perceives it as stolen, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1879"></a><strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:24.1"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he uses a robe(-cloth) which should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:24.2"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante atikkantasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days, but he perceives it as more than ten days, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:24.3"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:24.4"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante anatikkantasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days and he perceives it as less than ten days, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:25.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1880"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:25.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:25.3"
msgid "antodasāhaṃ adhiṭṭheti, vikappeti, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr "if within ten days it has been determined, transferred, given away, lost, destroyed, burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:25.4"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:25.5"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.1.5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1881"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:26.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ na denti."
msgstr "At that time monks from the group six did not give back relinquished robe(-cloth)."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:26.2"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They informed the Master."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.11"></a><strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:26.3"
msgid "() “Na, bhikkhave, nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ na dātabbaṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, relinquished robe(-cloth) should be given back."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:26.4"
msgid "Yo na dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "If a monk does not give it back, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. </strong></p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1882"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np1:27.1"
msgid "Kathinasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on the robe-making season, is finished."

